  <description><![CDATA[<p>The Design Hotel Levi mixes modern and traditional Lappish style. With beautifully designed rooms and a central position in Levi, you're close to the ski slopes, a variety of restaurants, cafes, and stores and access to the Spa Waterworld at the Levi Spa included. It ticks all of the boxes for a winter getaway.</p>
<h2>Luxurious rooms</h2>
<p>The Design Hotel is a relatively new accommodation in Levi, the hotel is furnished to a high standard with cosy communal areas and a range of luxurious rooms. Each room is labelled as 'Deluxe' and provides a welcome retreat after a days adventure, each room is furnished in a Lappish style yet has all the modern touches, encompassing grey pinewood, natural stones, black and copper finishes- all sourced from Finland. </p>
<h2>Art and design</h2>
<p>The Design Hotel Levi is the result of a collaboration between several Finnish and Nordic creators, resulting in a beautifully designed hotel. Mountain views are mixed with contemporary Nordic interior design, architecture, sculpture, light installations, and visual art. The rooms' structural elements are adorned with large-scale photography prints by nature photographer Kaisa Sirén. While contemporary sculptures by Risto Immonen and paintings by Hanna Kanto embellish the reception and lounge area.</p>
<h2>Soothing spa and leisure areas</h2>
<p>The Levi Spa Resort has a wide range of facilities for you to enjoy, including the amazing indoor/outdoor Spa Waterworld that is included in your stay. The indoor waterpark is one of the best in Finland, and provides fun for the whole family. It has a wide variety of indoor pools, waterslides, as well as saunas, Jacuzzis, and an outdoor pool. There's even a special section just for the little ones to enjoy. You can also arrange and pay for local services such as massages and spa treatments as well as fitness facilities like yoga and a gym if you want to stay fit.</p>
<p>The Design Hotel Levi is a part of the Levi Hotel Spa Resort, which features a number of different restaurants, ranging from pizza and burgers to local cuisine and fine dining restaurants that focus on Lappish food with modern twists.</p>]]></description>
